title: Class A rankings breakdown: Week 7
text:
Defeated Mid-Valley 26-0. Previously not ranked. 
Honorable Mention: Frazier (6-0),Portage (5-1), Neshannock (5-1), Jeanette (5-1), Clarion Area (5-1) Clairton - will take on Serra Catholic at home. The Bears let Jeanette hang around for a little bit last week until they put them away for good. The number two team is right on their heels for the number one spot. Bishop Guilfoyle - will take on Cambria Heights on the road. The Marauders are mauling teams left and right. Evan Chadbourne and Aaron Yasulitis both scored three touchdowns in their last win. North Catholic - will take on Avonworth on the road. Quarterback Erick Taylor ran for two touchdowns and passed for another two in North Catholic's win last week. Camp Hill - will take on Palmyra on the road. Running back Bill Williams ran for 121 yards and three touchdowns in last week's win against Steel-High. Sharpsville - will take on Eisenhower on the road. Khaliq Ragster ran 16 times for 127 yards and two touchdowns and a receiving touchdown in his team's win over Lakeview. Berlin Brothers Valley - will take on Meyersdale Area on the road. Running back Braden Fochtman ran 14 times for 147 yards and a touchdown in his team's win last week. Farrell - will take on Grove City on the road. Damond Burton collected one sack, nine tackles, and one tack for Farrell in their win over Bishop Kearney. Moshannon Valley - will take on Glendale at home. Greensburg Central Catholic - will take on Wilkinsburg on the road. Old Forge - will take on Lackawanna Trail at home.
